  "title": "Security Manager (Tuas/Shift/Up to $8000) Ref: JY",
  "description": "<p>Lead the design, implementation, and operation of security frameworks for high-risk, Protected Place (PP) laboratory facilities in Singapore. The role is accountable for end-to-end PP application, regulatory compliance, security operations, audits, and incident response, in accordance with the Protected Areas and Protected Places Act (Cap. 256), BATA, and related regulations.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><ul><li>Lead end-to-end Protected Place (PP) application, approval, and ongoing compliance with SPF (CPS), including Security-by-Design documentation and SS 668 alignment.</li><li>Design and implement integrated physical security and biosecurity frameworks for laboratory environments, including zoning, access control, and CPTED principles.</li><li>Establish and enforce staff and visitor access management, monitoring, and training within PP zones.</li><li>Act as primary liaison for security, biosafety, and emergency audits with SPF, MOH, SCDF, and other authorities.</li><li>Develop and lead incident response and crisis management plans; serve as Incident Commander during security or safety events.</li><li>Oversee security technologies (ACS, VSS, IDS, GSOC platforms) to ensure PP compliance and real-time monitoring.</li><li>Lead security teams and vendors, and manage security budgets with a focus on compliance, resilience, and cost efficiency.</li></ul><p></p></p><p><em><strong>Yee Jie Ling Jaslin (R1440114)</strong></em><br /><em><strong>Business Edge Personnel Services Pte Ltd (96C4864)</strong></em></p><p></p>",
